                     <p> 
                        <persName nymRef="Tonge">
                           <forename>Thomas</forename>, son and heir of <persName>
                              <forename>Nicholas</forename> de <surname>Tonge</surname>
                           </persName>, burgess in the village of <placeName role="person" key="place_108633">Welyngton</placeName>
                        </persName>,
               grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> le <surname>French</surname>
                        </persName> and 
               <persName nymRef="French">
                           <forename>Agnes</forename> his wife</persName> four heads ("seliones") of land and
               eight buttes of land lying unconnected in the fields of <placeName key="place_108633">Welyngton</placeName>. 
               Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_108633">Welyngton</placeName> the Tuesday
               next after the feast of the Annunc. B. V. M., <origDate notBefore="1375-01-25" notAfter="1376-01-24">49 Ed. III</origDate>. 
               . </p>
